{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2016}} {{Infobox musical artist | name = 0010x0010 | background = non_performing_personnel | image = File:0010x0010 skirt.jpg | birth_name = Raymond Tijssen | alias = T3TSUO 303, GDPRDX, Mziah, | birth_date = | birth_place = [[Helmond]], Netherlands | origin = | genre = [[Acid techno]], [[techno]], [[deep house]], [[trip hop]], [[Ambient music|ambient]] | occupation = {{flatlist| * DJ * Music Producer * Director * [[Video Editor]] * Photographer * Artist}} | instrument = Synthesizer, drum machine, drums, percussion, bass guitar, guitar | years_active = | label = {{flatlist| * Cyberstate of Consciousness * Generation Acid * Coincidence Records * AYCB * Boysnoize Records}} | website = {{URL|0010x0010.com}} }}
'''0010x0010''' is a Dutch-born [[audiovisual art]]ist, currently living in Los Angeles.
==Early years== In his early years, being inspired by underground techno, he released a series of [[Gramophone record|vinyl records]] under various pseudonyms (only one using his real name) and he performed live [[acid techno]] sets at underground parties such as Acid Rain at Amsterdam Graansilo. During the recording sessions for one of the tracks he produced for ex [[Soul II Soul]] and [[The Shamen]] singer Victoria Wilson James's album on Sony Music,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Victoria-Wilson-James-Colorfields/release/591843|title=Victoria Wilson-James - Colorfields|website=Discogs|accessdate=11 July 2017}}</ref> it was suggested that he audition for the "De Bende van Venlo", a theatre piece based on a true crime story.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://theaterencyclopedie.nl/wiki/De_bende_van_Venlo_-_Stichting_Theaterwerkplaats_Limburg_Het_Kruis_van_Bourgondi%C3%AB_-_1997-07-04|title=De bende van Venlo - Stichting Theaterwerkplaats Limburg Het Kruis van Bourgondië - 1997-07-04 - TheaterEncyclopedie|website=theaterencyclopedie.nl|accessdate=11 July 2017}}</ref> He was cast in one of the lead roles and performed over thirty European shows.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nrc.nl/nieuws/1997/07/05/vooral-sfeer-en-spektakel-in-stuk-de-bende-van-venlo-7359654-a1211521|title=Vooral sfeer en spektakel in stuk De Bende van Venlo|website=nrc.nl|accessdate=11 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.volkskrant.nl/binnenland/toneelstuk-over-bende-van-venlo-begint-met-rap-gewetenloze-killers-een-gruwelijke-afslachting~a484780/|title=Toneelstuk over Bende van Venlo begint met rap 'Gewetenloze killers, een gruwelijke afslachting' – Binnenland – de Volkskrant|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.volkskrant.nl/theater/de-bende-van-venlo-zit-vol-met-gemiste-kansen~a494401/|title=De Bende van Venlo zit vol met gemiste kansen – Theater – de Volkskrant|publisher=}}</ref>
==Los Angeles== After the theatre experience, Universal / [[Island Records]] won the label-bidding and signed him as an artist and producer.He released one single and one video before he left the label due to creative differences and moved from London to Los Angeles to work on his art, film, photography and editing <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiewire.com/2011/01/in-the-works-new-doc-from-paris-is-burning-director-sundances-pariah-chicago-mob-boss-more-243995/|title=In the Works: New Doc from "Paris is Burning" Director, Sundance’s "Pariah," Chicago Mob Boss & More - IndieWire|first=Bryce J.|last=Renninger|website=www.indiewire.com|accessdate=11 July 2017}}</ref> career. He took a break from that to release the track ''LA Mellow'' (as D'ray), a collaboration with Dutch Dj, producer [[Gregor Salto]]. ''Ultimate Miami 2'', the album with ''LA Mellow'' and music by artists like [[Wiwek]], [[Zki & Dobre|Chocolate Puma]] and [[Sidney Samson]] reached No. 6 at Beatport's House top 100.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bptoptracker.com/artist/dray/298277/releases|title=D'RAY – Beatport Top Tracker|first=Julien|last=Mahin|publisher=}}</ref> In late 2015, he finished working as the visual supervisor<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.asiancemagazine.com/2010/07/31/interview-with-dutch-filmmaker-mziah|title=Interview with Dutch filmmaker mZiah – Asiance Magazine|publisher=}}</ref> of a documentary about Russian director [[Andrei Tarkovsky]] based on his diaries [[Time Within Time: The Diaries 1970–1986|Time within Time]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt2311128/fullcredits?ref_=tt_cl_sm#cast|title=Tarkovsky: Time Within Time|date=1 January 2000|publisher=|via=IMDb}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vice.com/read/tarkovsky-does-berlin-0817|title=Among the Tarkovsky Fanatics at an Underground Retrospective in Berlin – VICE – United States|date=18 August 2015|publisher=}}</ref> starring [[Tonino Guerra]]. In 2016, he released two EPs (as 0010x0010 and T3TSUO 303) on his Generation Acid label which both landed in the [[Beatport]] Techno Top 100 charts. The May 2017 released [[acid techno]] album |||Ø||| <ref>https://www.discogs.com/0010X0010-%C3%98/release/10234031</ref> made it to the techno and house top 10 charts on both [[Beatport]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bptoptracker.com/label/generation-acid/28924/releases|title=Generation Acid – Beatport Top Tracker|first=Julien|last=Mahin|publisher=}}</ref> and [[Juno Records]].
