{{Infobox musical artist | name = Mr 2Kay | image = | image_size = | landscape = <!-- yes, if wide image, otherwise leave blank --> | alt = | caption = | background = solo_singer | birth_name = Abinye David Jumbo | native_name = Abinye | native_name_lang = | alias = Mr 2Kay | birth_date = <!-- {{birth date and age|df=yes|1986|10|19|1986|10|19} --> | birth_place = [[Port Harcourt]], [[Rivers State]] Nigeria | origin = [[Rivers State]], [[Nigeria]] | death_date = <!-- {{death date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date 1st) --> | death_place = | genre = [[Afro pop music]] | occupation = Singer, songwriter, performer | instrument = Vocals | years_active = 2010–present | label = [[Grafton Entertainment]] | associated_acts = Prince Hezekiah, [[Ruggedman]], DJ Joenel, Nanas, Double K, Big Mouf, Sweet Gems, Valo, Hansmills, [[Duncan Mighty]], Aby, Spaceman | website = <!-- {{URL|www.example.com}} --> }}
'''Abinye David Jumbo''' better known as '''Mr 2Kay''', is a [[Nigerian]] singer and songwriter. He is signed to [[Grafton Entertainment]].<ref name="2Kay">{{cite news|title=New Kid from Grafton Records|url=http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/new-kid-from-grafton-records/109732/|accessdate=12 August 2015|work=Thisday Live|date=21 February 2012}}</ref>
==Early life==
Mr 2Kay was born in [[Port Harcourt]]. After his birth, his family moved to [[Bonny Island]], [[Rivers State]] where he grew up. 2Kay was also a good crafts man as he drew portraits while growing up.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mr 2Kay Biography|url=http://www.biographyhome.com/2014/08/mr-2Kay.html|publisher=Biography Home|accessdate=}}</ref>
Mr 2Kay started his music career in Port Harcourt and his break out single from Port Harcourt was waterside boy but it didn't break international on till 2012 when Mr 2Kay released Bubugaga which was his international break out single.
Mr 2Kay's debut single "Bubugaga" was released on 8 October 2012. The music video for "Bubugaga" was shot in [[London]], [[United Kingdom|UK]] and directed by Nosa Igbinedion under Grafton Entertainment. Which was his international hit single. Mr 2Kay's debut single "Waterside Boy" was released on 21 August 2011 under Grafton Entertainment. Which was his Port Harcourt hit single.<ref>{{cite news|title=Fighting Their Way to Stardom|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201401061760.html|accessdate=12 August 2015|work=[[AllAfrica]]|date=5 January 2014}}</ref>
==Personal life== ===Robbery Attack=== On 25 October 2017, Mr 2Kay was reportedly robbed by four armed men in his hotel room at [[Eko Hotels and Suites]] at [[Victoria Island, Lagos]] after performing at [[2Baba]]’s Buckwyld and Breathless Concert, which took place at the convention centre of Eko Hotel.<ref>{{cite news|title=Singer,.Mr. 2Kay battered, robbed at gunpoint - Vanguard News|url=https://www.vanguardngr.com/2017/10/singer-mr-2Kay-battered-robbed-gunpoint/|accessdate=8 November 2017|work=Vanguard News|publisher=[[Vanguard (Nigeria)|Vanguard]]|date=25 October 2017}}</ref> 2Kay was left with injuries sustain from the robbery, also totally bound, arms, legs and mouth while the robbers left with his valuables which include, clothes, jewelry, phones, perfumes, and money. 1 week after robbery Mr 2Kay released a new single "Pray for Me" which was scheduled for a late November release alongside with his forthcoming album which is currently on hold due to the incident his label, [[Grafton Entertainment|Grafton Records]] has to push the album release date.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mr. 2Kay - Pray For Me [New Music] {{!}} BellaNaija|url=https://www.bellanaija.com/2017/11/new-music-mr-2Kay-pray/|website=[[BellaNaija]]|accessdate=8 November 2017}}</ref> On 7 November 2017, Mr 2Kay reportedly filed a 500 millionaire lawsuit against the management of [[Eko Hotels and Suites]] where the incident happened in October.<ref>{{cite news|title=ROBBERY ATTACK: Mr 2Kay slams N500m lawsuit on Eko Hotel|url=https://www.ripplesnigeria.com/robbery-attack-mr-2Kay-slams-n500m-lawsuit-eko-hotel/|accessdate=8 November 2017|work=Ripples Nigeria|publisher=Ripples Nigeria|date=7 November 2017}}</ref>
==Notable performances== He has performed in several popular events and shows since his rise to stardom, performed in events like: *Factory78 TV – Mr 2Kay Performs Bubugaga Live / Face-off interview in 2012 <ref>{{cite web|title=FACTORY78 – Mr 2Kay Performs Bubugaga Live / Face-off interview|url=http://naijacelebrity.com.ng/2012/11/22/factory78-mr-2Kay-performs-bubugaga-live-face-off-interview/|publisher=Naija Celebrity|accessdate=}}</ref> *Afrobeats London Party at Coronet in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|title=Afrobeats London Party at Coronet|url=https://shoobs.com/events/3964/afrobeat-sundays|publisher=shoobs|accessdate=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Afrobeats London Party at Coronet|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xN_HAbQGvOQ|publisher=[[YouTube]] ([[Tonye Ibiama]])|accessdate=}}</ref> * Carniriv Closing Ceremony In 2014.<ref>{{cite web|title=mr 2Kay performance at Caniriv 2014 closing ceremony|url=http://pulse.ng/music/mr-2Kay-watch-singer-thrill-20-000-fans-at-carniriv-id3411689.html|publisher=Pulse Nigeria|accessdate=}}</ref> *Prestigious London Jazz cafe IN 2014.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mr 2Kay performs at Prestigious London Jazz cafe|url=http://jaguda.com/2014/07/30/pictures-mr-2Kay-thrills-london-jazz-cafe/|publisher=Jaguda|accessdate=}}</ref> *All Africa Music Awards (AFRIMA) At Industry Nite in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=Watch Cynthia Morgan, Mr 2Kay, Niniola, others perform at AFRIMA Industry Nite|url=http://pulse.ng/buzz/pulse-tv-exclusive-watch-cynthia-morgan-mr-2Kay-niniola-others-perform-at-afrima-industry-nite-id3934685.html|publisher=Pulse Tv|accessdate=}}</ref>
===Concert tour=== On Sunday, 17 June 2018, at Aztech Arcum Stadium Road [[Port Harcourt]], [[Rivers State]] Nigeria. Mr 2Kay kickoff with his album concert "Elevated" features guest artist, radio host/hype man<ref>{{cite web |title=Mr 2Kay Defends His Claim Of Elevation With His Successful Elevation Concert In Port Harcourt {{!}} See Photos - Nigerian Entertainment Today |url=http://thenet.ng/mr-2Kay-defends-claim-elevation-successful-elevation-concert-port-harcourt-see-photos/ |website=[[Nigerian Entertainment Today]] |accessdate=27 June 2018 |date=19 June 2018}}</ref> & disc jockeys<ref>{{cite web |title=Mr 2Kay to feature top deejays at ‘The Elevated Concert’ - The Nation Nigeria |url=http://thenationonlineng.net/mr-2Kay-to-feature-top-deejays-at-the-elevated-concert/ |website=[[The Nation (Nigeria)|The Nation Nigeria]] |accessdate=27 June 2018 |date=27 May 2018}}</ref> [[Timaya]], [[Duncan Mighty]], [[Harrysong]], Charles Okocha, [[DJ Jimmy Jatt]], [[DJ Neptune]], [[DJ Big N]], DJ Kev, Joenell, Ayi, Real Prince, Idahams, Doray, Young GreyC, [[Squeeze Tarela]], Legendary Sunny, Ajebo Hustlers, King Perryy, [[M Trill]], Korkormikor, [[Olisa Adibua]], Shope Shopsy and Alex from [[Big Brother Naija (season 3)]]. The concert was recorded sold out with a capacity of over 2000 (two thousand) sitters <ref>{{cite web |title=Shut Down! Over 2,000 People Gathered For Mr 2Kay's ELEVATED Concert - Nigerian Entertainment Today |url=http://thenet.ng/shut-2000-people-gathered-mr-2Kays-elevated-concert/ |website=[[Nigerian Entertainment Today]] |accessdate=27 June 2018 |date=18 June 2018}}</ref>, ticket where sold within the rage of (₦2,000 - ₦500,000)<ref>{{cite web |title=Mr 2Kay Elevated Concert {{!}} NETShop |url=https://buy.thenet.ng/event/mr-2Kay-elevated-concert/ |website=NETShop |accessdate=27 June 2018}}</ref>
Mr 2Kay posted on his social media page's on 2 April 2018, to announce a singing/dancing competition<ref>{{cite web |title=MR. 2Kay Set To Hold Elevated Concert, And Give Back To Port Harcourt This June - Nigerian Entertainment Today |url=http://thenet.ng/mr-2Kay-set-hold-elevated-concert-give-back-port-harcourt-june/ |website=[[Nigerian Entertainment Today]] |accessdate=27 June 2018 |date=28 March 2018}}</ref> where he’ll be giving away $2000 (Two Thousand Dollars) to 2 persons in [[Port Harcourt]]. {{cquote|According to him, the initiative is a way of giving back to his starting foundation in the music industry. “Call it my little way of giving back to a place where I started my career. }}
